ENTRY            M0813   20260115   20260226   20260226       M143
SUBENT        M0813001   20260115   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                 10         34
TITLE      Fragments yields in spontaneous and photo-fission  of
            Cm-248.
AUTHOR     (Yu.P.Gangrsky,V.I.Zhemenik,N.Yu.Maslova,
           G.V.Myshinsky,Yu.E.Penionzhkevich)
REFERENCE  (J,PPN/L,2,92,2005)
            English translation of FCY/L,2,(2),44,2005
           (J,FCY/L,2,(2),44,2005).
           (C,2004BELGOR,,80,2004)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,4UKRIJD)
FACILITY   (MICRT,4ZZZDUB) Microtron  MT-25 of the Laboratory of
            Nuclear Reaction of the Joint Institute for  Nuclear
            Research, Dubna.
REL-REF    (M,M0811001,Yu.P.Gangrsky+,J,PPN/L,7,(6),415,2010)
            Facility description.
           (O,41557001,Yu.P.Gangrskii+,J,FCY/L,2,(2),44,2005)
            Data from Tables 1,2 for photo-/spontaneous fission
            ratios were compiled.
SAMPLE     CmO2 oxide (15 mm diameter, 0.6 mg/cm**2 thickness,
            Ti backing of 1.5 micron thickness).
            2.E+18 number of 248Cm nuclei.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Ge-detector (150 cm**3 volume, 2.1 keV
            resolution for 1133 keV gamma-line (60Co)).
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on sources.
HISTORY    (20110401C) Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
            CDFE by V.Varlamov.
           (20141111A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REFERENCE -
            PPN/L added.
           (20151225A) Corrected by SD ad VV: METHOD, STATUS
            ("COREL" deleted), REL-REF (added), corrections
            in SUBENT 002, SUBENT 003 added.
           (20191001U) Corrected by V.Varlamov: HISTORY (line
            2011), REACTION, STATUS, MONITOR, DATA.
           (20260115T) Corrected by V.Varlamov: TITLE, REFERENCE,
            SAMPLE, METHOD, STATUS, SUBENT 004 added.
ENDBIB              34
COMMON               1          3
EN-MAX
MEV
   25.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           41
SUBENT        M0813002   20260115   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                  5         17
REACTION  1(96-CM-248(G,F)ELEM/MASS,IND,FY,,BRA)
          2((96-CM-248(G,F)ELEM/MASS,IND,FY,,BRA)/
           (96-CM-248(G,F)36-KR-90,IND,FY,,BRA))
MONITOR    (96-CM-248(G,F)36-KR-90,IND,FY,,BRA)
METHOD     (GSPEC) Kr and Xe isotopes were identified by the
            decay gammas emitted by them or by their daughters
            for short-lived (T1/2<1 min) Kr and Xe isotopes.
           (HEJET) Only Kr and Xe isotopes having T1/2 > 0.2 sec
            and their decay products were transported and
            measured.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.P.Gangrsky,J,PPN/L,2,92,2005)
            Data from Table 2.
