SUBENT        M0813004   20260115   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                  6         24
REACTION   ((96-CM-248(G,F)ELEM/MASS,CUM,FY,,BRA)/
           (96-CM-248(0,F)ELEM/MASS,CUM,FY))
           Cumulative yields ratio of photo-fission to
            spontaneous fission of Cm-248.
REL-REF    (R,L0050016,J.T.Caldwell+,J,PR/C,21,1215,1980)
           (N,,Ph.Kondev+,J,NIM/B,71,126,1992)
           Method for the calculation of bremsstrahlung spectra
            produced by electrons.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Fission fragments were collected on Al foil
            of 20 micron thickness, place at 0.5 mm distance
            from Cm layer during 200 hr for SF, 6 hr for photo-
            fission.
           After cooling of a week, gamma-spectra were measured
            during several months to define half-lives.
           To identify  fission fragment the data were used from
            the book: Yu.P.Gangrskiy+, Nuclei fission fragments,
            Moscow, Energoizdat,1986.
           (GSPEC) Yields were defined from its gamma-spectra.
ANALYSIS    Gamma-lines areas were used to define fission
            yields.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.P.Gangrsky,J,PPN/L,2,92,2005)
            Data from Table 1.
HISTORY    (20260115T) Corrected by V.Varlamov: SUBENT is moved
            from 41557004.
ENDBIB              24
